OL,7,FMr Jones asked "Would you have told
OL,8,FElaine it wasn't possible to do a
OL,9,Fcomplete mastectomy?"
OL,11,FPaterson replied "No, because all of
OL,12,Fus do our best to remove all visible
OL,13,Fbreast tissue, but it is a worrying
OL,14,Fand frightening detail to tell them
OL,15,Fthere may be deposits of breast tissue
OL,16,Fleft behind which could see a local
OL,17,Frecurrence (of cancer).
OL,19,F"The nurses would have mentioned it as
OL,20,Fa possibility in the future as part of
OL,21,Fthe preparation."
OL,26,@oD@POUqD@UO]sD@ROU{D@AOU}D@QO]
